title: For Sale/Trade:  6.5 Grendel complete upper and scope
postcontent: I finished this build about a month ago with the addition of the Leupold Mark AR scope.Reciever, bolt carrier, and hand guard are from Radical Arms. The Barrel, and Bolt are from Brownells, and i believe are satern manufactured I bead blasted the barrel for a more matte gray finish than stock.every thing was checked for square uppon assembly and barrel torqued to 53lbs (according to my bench notes).Accuracy at 100yds has been sub 1" with most groups averaging less than .5"s, these were all shot during rough load work up. I have not finalized the loads for this uppper, but so far 31.5grn of cfe223 behind a 123amax is showing promise, id suggest the new owner work around that range to see what comes up as the best. Ive shot my steel plate out to 500yds with this rig in its semi tuned fashion and making consistent hits is not that difficult.The scope is a Leupold Mark AR, older model that has the better turret covers. its a 6-18x40, has a forward objective focus ring, and the CDC turrets for a 5.56 (if your inclined you can purchase turrets for any cal and load from Leupold for bout 60 bucks a set). Dail ups have been accurate and consistent and return to zero has been perfect. It comes with the buttler creek caps.Rings are cheap aluminums, but when checked for alignment theye were perfect on this upper. Ive replaced with shitty over size nobs with decent nylock stainless hardware.Bipods a utg and is actually pretty good quality, i didnt build this upper for serious knock around hunting, so the cheaper bipod works fine for what i do. If you plan on really beating on the rig tho a tougher pod might be in order.first picture is of when i first completed the upper and was working on initial load development, optics and barrel finish are visible in second picture.Any questions feel free to hit me upIll trade for other gun or bow stuff450 no scopethanksKeao3152000
